Our first artist is Scaro "Stephen Challener" Dactyl. Gem trader by day, pixel artist by night, this arm enthusiast provided graphics for Homestuck, and has returned with a double helping of retro schmaltz for Hiveswap. Get ready for a blast to the past, as we revisit the 90s with some new takes on classic graphics and gameplay!
"When WhatPumpkin first approached me to work on the Hiveswap project, I thought they were joking. The idea of creating an entire subsection of the game era-appropriate pixel art style, it seemed insane! But when I saw how it fit into Hussie's grand vision I knew it was the right thing to do. I hope you like this small cross-section of what is in store!"

In a world as dangerous as Alternia you'll need powerful friends and allies. This is just one of the many richly-plotted characters you might meet on your journey. He may be a wiggler, but make no mistake, this grub is large and in charge! Will you find favor with this executive meddler, or will your existence be made redundant? Only you can determine the outcome.
Enjoy these snippets of tracks in the game!
